ames © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish: nickname from Middle English <i>mody</i> ‘proud, haughty, angry, fierce, bold, brave, or rash’ (Old English <i>mōdig</i>). Compare   Muddiman  . This English name has been established in Ireland since the late 13th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Woody","meanings":["English:","from Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘wood’ + <i>heie</i> ‘enclosure’ (Old English <i>wudu</i> + <i>(ge)hæg</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived by an enclosure in a wood, or habitational, for a person from a place so named, such as Woodhey Green in Faddiley (Cheshire). Also possibly from East Woodhay (Hampshire) and West Woodhay (Berkshire), apparently named with Old English <i>wīd</i> ‘wide, broad’ as the initial element, confused with early Old English <i>widu</i> ‘wood’, and so too with Old English <i>wudu</i>.","nickname from Middle English <i>wodi</i> or some other derivative of Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘frenzied, wild’ (Old English <i>wōd</i>), perhaps formed on the analogy of, for example, Middle English <i>mody</i> (see   Moody  ). Compare   Wood   2."]},{"name":"Muddiman","meanings":["English (Northamptonshire): nickname from Middle English <i>mody</i> ‘proud, haughty, angry, fierce, bold, brave, rash’ (Old English <i>mōdig</i>) + <i>man</i> ‘man’. See   Moody  ."]},{"name":"Mooty","meanings":["English: variant of   Moody  . This form of the surname is rare in Britain.","Possibly an Americanized form of German <b>Mutig</b>, a nickname meaning ‘cheerful’."]},{"name":"Moodie","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Moody  ."]},{"name":"Moudy","meanings":["English (London): variant of   Moody  . This form of the surname is rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Mowdy","meanings":["English or Irish: variant of   Moody  ."]},{"name":"Mudie","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scottish Iain.","English and Scottish (Angus): variant of   Moody  ."]}]},{"name":"Sir.","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Simon  , now rare, but more common in the Middle Ages, when it gave rise to the surnames <i>Simms</i> and <i>Simpson</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Simon","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]},{"name":"Ugn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of English <b>Hugh</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Sr.","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘light; beauty; prosperity’, also ‘rank, power, royal majesty’, a byname of the goddesses Lakshmi and Saraswati. Also widely used as an honorific title."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir. Ugn Sr. Moody was born about 1330, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1330–":"umbes 1330–Surnud","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","about 1330":"umbes 1330","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1330–":"noin 1330–Kuollut","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","about 1330":"noin 1330","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1330–":"environ 1330–Décédé","1360–Male":"1360–Décédé","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","about 1330":"environ 1330","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir. Ugn Sr. Moody est né environ 1330, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1330–":"um 1330–Verstorben","1360–Male":"1360–Verstorben","1330–Male":"1330–Versto